:: StoryTitle
Within Limits

:: StoryData
{
  "ifid": "804A7958-43A9-462D-B7CC-ADF345205DD3",
  "format": "SugarCube",
  "format-version": "2.37.3",
  "start": "FlightPrep"
}

:: StoryInit
/* Scenario metadata
   SCENARIO TITLE:      Within Limits
   AUDIENCE:            Pilot (GA, 500-1,000 hr; protagonist ~640 TT, PPL/IR)
   TONE:                Professional
   PRIMARY TOPIC:       Passenger pressure from an intelligent non-pilot;
                        PIC authority when the argument cannot be won on debate points
   SECONDARY TOPIC:     Ambiguous mechanical evidence (magneto discrepancy);
                        diagnosis vs. rationalization; outcome bias
   AIRCRAFT/EQUIPMENT:  1999 Piper Saratoga II HP (PA-32R-301), N429TC.
                        Lycoming IO-540-K1G5 300 hp, dual Slick magnetos,
                        102 gal usable, Garmin 430W + KX 155, KAP 150 autopilot.
   SETTING:             Alpine-Casparis Muni (E38), Alpine TX, elev 4,514.
                        Sunday afternoon in June, hot. Fuel stop on the way home
                        from a Big Bend hiking weekend. Field unattended Sundays.
                        Home: San Marcos Regional (KHYI), 273 nm ENE.
   WEATHER:             Severe clear, hot, light wind. Density altitude ~7,600.
                        The weather is not the problem.
   ADM THEMES:          External pressure, PIC authority, unproven diagnosis,
                        the difference between "within limits" and "understood,"
                        outcome bias, evidence-buying (test flight, delay)
   HAZARDOUS ATTITUDES: Impulsivity (launch now), macho (argue and win),
                        resignation (he's smarter, he's probably right),
                        invulnerability (it cleared, we're fine)
   TOTAL DECISIONS:     Branching; every path passes 4+ decision points
   TOTAL ENDINGS:       11 (success x3, qualified x2, friction x2,
                        delay/diversion x3, aircraft damage x1, fatal x0)
   MIN DECISION DEPTH:  4
   TIMED DECISIONS:     No
   ESTIMATED DURATION:  20-30 minutes
   VERSION:             1.0
   LAST REVIEWED:       2026-07-06
   REVIEWER:            Claude (initial draft) / Harvey Madison (pending)

   Facts verified against FAA/AirNav data June 2026 cycle: E38 elevation
   4,514.4; runways 1/19 6002x75 (fair) and 5/23 5018x60 (good); CTAF/UNICOM
   122.8; AWOS-3 119.025; unattended Sundays; self-serve 100LL 24 hr;
   ABQ Center via Fort Stockton RCAG 135.875; MRF VOR/DME 115.9 r059/15;
   RNAV (GPS) 19 and 23; ODKAE ONE obstacle DP; special takeoff minimums.
   KOZA 16/34 6003x75. KJCT 17/35 5004x75. KFST 12/30 7508x100.
   KHYI towered, ATIS 120.825, tower 126.825.
*/
<<set $pathArray to []>>
<<set $badchoices to 0>>
<<set $readWeather to false>>
<<set $readFlightPlan to false>>
<<set $readAircraft to false>>
<<set $readField to false>>
<<set $methodical to false>>   /* compared both mags deliberately at D1 */
<<set $vmNote to false>>       /* left Werner a voicemail */
<<set $vmReply to false>>      /* his text arrived (timing varies by path) */
<<set $plugPulled to false>>   /* pulled and inspected a bottom plug */
<<set $tested to false>>       /* flew the pattern test profile */
<<set $testShowedDrop to false>>
<<set $delayed to false>>      /* waited out the heat before launching */
<<set $heatSoak to false>>     /* launched hot: the fault's favorite weather */
<<set $missBegan to false>>    /* the right mag started arcing en route */
<<set $routing to "">>         /* "direct", "corridor", "overhead" */
<<set $stretched to false>>    /* tried to stretch past the last good option */
<<set $isolated to false>>     /* identified it with an in-flight mag check */
<<set $singleMag to false>>    /* elected to run on the left mag */
<<set $divert to "">>          /* "", "KOZA", "KFST", "E38", "KJCT" */
<<set $pressOn to 0>>          /* times a divert was declined after the miss */
<<set $grantSaw to false>>     /* Grant witnessed the recurrence himself */

