:: End_KJCT_Dusk [scenario ending]
<<set $pathArray to $pathArray.concat(["Ending: Junction, in the last of the light"])>>

Junction's runway lights are already up when you join the pattern, and the landing happens in that blue ten minutes where the world is all silhouette and beacon. <<if $singleMag>>The left mag flies the approach without a tremor, which you refuse to find reassuring on principle.<<else>>The engine holds its manners through the pattern, one small shiver in the flare, as if signing its work.<</if>> You shut down in front of a dark FBO with I-10's river of headlights pouring past beyond the fence.

Grant surveys the empty ramp, the vending machine's glow, the first stars. "I have slept in worse towns for worse reasons," he says, and has the motel's number dialed before you finish the chains. Tuesday, a mechanic from Kerrville makes the drive, benches the mag, and finds the carbon track. The last hundred miles home take thirty-eight minutes and feel like a victory lap someone else paid for.

<hr>
<div class="debrief">
<h3>What happened</h3>
<p>You carried the problem <<if $pressOn gte 2>>a long way past its first exit<<elseif $pressOn gte 1>>past at least one good exit<<else>>to the edge of night<</if>> and then, at Junction, stopped carrying it: a runway taken with power available, options open, and nothing bent. The airplane spent two nights in Junction. Nobody remembers that part in a year; that's the point of it.</p>
<h3>ADM analysis</h3>
<p><<if $pressOn gte 2>>Look honestly at the shape of this path: the engine asked for attention, and got it only after multiple refusals, each individually defensible, each narrowing the next choice. The chain broke because you finally broke it, in nearly the last place with lights. Credit for the break; the audit belongs to the links.<<elseif $isolated>>The isolation gave you truth, and Junction is where the truth finally outweighed the totalizer's twenty-minutes-to-home arithmetic. Earlier would have been cheaper; later would have been expensive in a different currency.<<else>>Stopping at Junction with climb power still on request is the definition of using margin while it's still margin.<</if>> The dusk matters more than it feels like it does at the time: every minute later converts a precautionary landing into a night precautionary landing, which is a different and worse instrument.</p>
<h3>What good judgment looks like here</h3>
<p>When a known-degraded system is flying you toward darkness, the last lighted runway before the empty stretch is not one of the options; it is the option, and it should be briefed that way out loud ("Junction or we declare"). The versions of this evening that skipped Junction appear elsewhere in this scenario, and they are not better stories.</p>
<h3>Key takeaway</h3>
<p>Margins spend like daylight: invisibly, then all at once. Land while stopping is still a choice and not a result.</p>
</div>
<div class="restart">
<<link "Return to Start" "FlightPrep">><<set $pathArray to []>><<set $badchoices to 0>><<set $readWeather to false>><<set $readFlightPlan to false>><<set $readAircraft to false>><<set $readField to false>><<set $methodical to false>><<set $vmNote to false>><<set $vmReply to false>><<set $plugPulled to false>><<set $tested to false>><<set $testShowedDrop to false>><<set $delayed to false>><<set $heatSoak to false>><<set $missBegan to false>><<set $routing to "">><<set $stretched to false>><<set $isolated to false>><<set $singleMag to false>><<set $divert to "">><<set $pressOn to 0>><<set $grantSaw to false>><</link>>
</div>
