:: End_RanchRoad [scenario ending]
<<set $pathArray to $pathArray.concat(["Ending: the caliche road"])>>

<<if $stretched>>The stretch toward Fredericksburg's glow lasts four minutes. The engine's recoveries get shorter, the sags get deeper, and the glide math finally speaks in a voice louder than hope: the glow is seventeen miles away and the airplane has nine of them. You come back to the road you passed, lower now, fewer choices in the dark, and take what the flashlight and the landing light can build.

The caliche is wide and mostly straight. The airplane arrives fast and flat, touches once, skips, and the second arrival finds the washout the first one warned you about. The nose gear folds. The prop finds the road. N429TC slides two hundred yards on its nose bowl and comes to rest tilted into the fence line, and then it is very, very quiet.<<else>>You fly it like an approach, because that's what it is: power set on the good seconds, flaps on schedule, Grant's flashlight steady on the road, gear down onto the wide caliche with the last of the engine's cooperation. The touchdown is honest. The rollout isn't: a cattle-guard dip a quarter mile in takes the nose gear, and the airplane slides the last hundred feet on its cowl, prop bent back like grass in the wind, and stops.<</if>>

Headsets off. The tick of metal. Grant's voice, carefully level: "Are we done? I'd like to be done."

You are done. Doors open, both of you out and upright in the sudden enormous dark, a bruise starting where the shoulder strap did its work. The ELT is chirping to satellites. A ranch house porch light comes on a half mile off, and a dog announces you to the county.

<hr>
<div class="debrief">
<h3>What happened</h3>
<p>A heat-activated magneto fault, first observed at the run-up pad, was carried through <<print $pressOn>> declined exits until the failing unit stopped being intermittent at night over ranch country. <<if $stretched>>The last decision, stretching for a glow instead of committing to the surface in reach, spent the remaining altitude on distance and paid for it with control of the arrival.<<else>>The forced landing itself was flown with discipline, which is why this debrief is being read by its participants.<</if>> Two people walked away. The airplane didn't.</p>
<h3>ADM analysis</h3>
<p>Chain endings deserve chain debriefs, so name the links. A cleared-but-unexplained run-up accepted as resolved. A heat-soaked launch over the route's worst terrain. <<if not $isolated>>A failure never fully diagnosed.<<else>>A diagnosis made and then outvoted.<</if>> Ozona declined. Junction declined. <<if $stretched>>A glide spent on hope instead of geometry.<<else>>And then the engine ended the voting.<</if>> No single link looks fatal, and none was: this ending exists five decisions deep, every one of them reversible at the time. That is how these arrive in the real world too. Not as one bad call, but as a hallway of doors, each quietly closing.</p>
<h3>What good judgment looks like here</h3>
<p>Any earlier ending in this scenario. Failing those: exactly what the final minutes contained on the disciplined branch, an arrival flown under control to a chosen surface with the airplane's energy spent on the pilot's terms. The FAA's forced-landing guidance and every glider pilot alive agree on the core: fly the machine all the way to the stop, and choose the crash you can walk from over the airport you can't reach. <<if $stretched>>The glow on the horizon is the last trap on the route: seventeen miles of maybe against nine miles of certainty is not a close call, and at night it only ever feels like one.<</if>></p>
<h3>Key takeaway</h3>
<p>Nobody plans to bet an airplane on a magneto. It happens one reasonable-sounding mile at a time. The road home was paved with exits, and the last one out here was made of caliche.</p>
</div>
<div class="restart">
<<link "Return to Start" "FlightPrep">><<set $pathArray to []>><<set $badchoices to 0>><<set $readWeather to false>><<set $readFlightPlan to false>><<set $readAircraft to false>><<set $readField to false>><<set $methodical to false>><<set $vmNote to false>><<set $vmReply to false>><<set $plugPulled to false>><<set $tested to false>><<set $testShowedDrop to false>><<set $delayed to false>><<set $heatSoak to false>><<set $missBegan to false>><<set $routing to "">><<set $stretched to false>><<set $isolated to false>><<set $singleMag to false>><<set $divert to "">><<set $pressOn to 0>><<set $grantSaw to false>><</link>>
