:: End_Caught_Overnight [scenario ending]
<<set $pathArray to $pathArray.concat(["Ending: the fault confessed overhead the field"])>>

<<if $pathArray.includes("Got Grant a car and rolling east")>>The rental outfit's after-hours number answers on the fourth try, and by 7:30 Grant is eastbound in a dusty crossover with two gas-station coffees and his outline recited into his phone. He makes San Antonio by half past midnight and a federal courtroom by eight, on schedule and running on fumes of several kinds. His text arrives as you're chaining the airplane: "Home. Your move was right and so was mine. Family holiday story secured."<<else>>Grant makes the call from the pilot lounge, absorbs a performance of inconvenience from opposing counsel, and moves the deposition to Wednesday. "He'll dine out on this favor for a year," he says, pocketing the phone. "Cheap at the price." You split a motel, a diner table, and the kind of evening conversation that only happens after an airplane has settled an argument for you.<</if>>

Tuesday morning the Alpine shop puts the right mag on the bench and finds the carbon track across the distributor block inside the first half hour: a scorched pencil line of wandering spark, heat-activated, exactly the kind of fault that passes a cold check and fails a hot climb.

<hr>
<div class="debrief">
<h3>What happened</h3>
<p>You refused to let a cleared number close an unexplained case, and you built the one experiment that could reopen it: full power, real heat, real load, with a runway directly below. The fault attended. From that moment the scenario stopped being a judgment problem and became a logistics problem, which is the happiest demotion in aviation.</p>
<h3>ADM analysis</h3>
<p>The test-overhead profile is the counterintuitive-but-correct move at the heart of this scenario: it spends fuel and minutes to convert an argument into an observation. Note what it did to the social pressure: it didn't defeat Grant's argument, it made the argument moot. Evidence is the only thing that ever truly ends a debate with a smart passenger, because it's the only thing that lets them lose without losing face.</p>
<h3>What good judgment looks like here</h3>
<p>Exactly this shape. Treat an unproven diagnosis as unproven. Design the cheapest observation that can distinguish the stories, and run it where the consequences of the bad story are smallest. And then handle the humans. <<if $pathArray.includes("Got Grant a car and rolling east")>>Sending Grant east by road traded your risk domain for his: five hours of dark two-lane is not free, and it was his call to make in his own domain, made with open eyes.<<else>>Advising the continuance priced the night drive honestly: a tired man doing five hours of dark two-lane is the same unproven-system bet you'd just declined, wearing different equipment.<</if>></p>
<h3>Key takeaway</h3>
<p>When the numbers pass but the engine already testified once, build a test the fault can fail. Ten minutes over the field is the cheapest magneto bench in Texas.</p>
</div>
<div class="restart">
