:: End_Overnight_Shop [scenario ending]
<<set $pathArray to $pathArray.concat(["Ending: the bench before the flight"])>>

You taxi the two hundred yards to the open hangar and the day gets simple. The mechanic listens to ninety seconds of your story, nods at "cleared after a lean burn-off," and has the right mag off the engine before his coffee cools. The distributor block comes out with a carbon track burned across it like a dry riverbed.

"There's your ghost," he says. "Cold check passes. Get it good and hot under load, spark starts commuting by the scenic route. Next hot day it quits being intermittent." He has a block in stock for the Slick, because out here he stocks what the desert breaks. You're airborne by 1:30 and home by hangar-door dusk. Grant, deposed and victorious at one o'clock, texts at four: "Tell the magneto I said nothing personal."

<hr>
<div class="debrief">
<h3>What happened</h3>
<p>The overnight bought exactly what it promised: a Monday morning where the discrepancy could be handed to someone with a bench instead of argued with. The fault was found in thirty minutes, fixed in ninety, and the flight home was flown behind an ignition system with no secrets in it.</p>
<h3>ADM analysis</h3>
<p>The choice this ending rewards is the refusal to let a clean cold check retire a hot-engine question, which is a different thing from caution for its own sake. That distinction, cold evidence versus hot question, ran the whole scenario, and the shop's diagnosis names it: some faults only exist at temperature. A run-up is a thermometer reading taken in the shade.</p>
<h3>What good judgment looks like here</h3>
<p>When the fix is two hundred yards away and open for business, the cost-benefit table has a column most Sundays don't: certainty, same-day, cheap. Taking it converted every remaining unknown in this scenario into a receipt. The alternative (fly it home cold and scope it Thursday) was defensible and is its own ending; the difference between them is three days of carrying a question you could have answered before lunch.</p>
<h3>Key takeaway</h3>
<p>If the bench is within taxi distance, the bench goes first. Certainty is rarely this conveniently located; when it is, buy it.</p>
</div>
