:: End_Deadline_Drive [scenario ending]
<<set $pathArray to $pathArray.concat(["Ending: Grant drives; the airplane waits for the bench"])>>

The rental outfit's after-hours voicemail calls back at 7:40, and by 8:15 Grant is eastbound in the only car on the lot, seat racked forward, deposition outline playing through the speakers in his own recorded voice. It is three hundred and seventy road miles to San Antonio. He texts from a gas station in Sonora at 10:50 ("alive, caffeinated, rehearsing") and from his driveway at 1:15 a.m. ("home. we are never speaking of this weekend under oath").

You stay with the airplane. Monday morning the Alpine shop opens at eight, finds the carbon-tracked distributor block by nine, and has you airborne by noon. Grant performs his deposition on five hours of sleep and wins it anyway, because of course he does.

<hr>
<div class="debrief">
<h3>What happened</h3>
<p>You held the airplane on the ground and the calendar found another way to San Antonio: five hours of dark two-lane, driven by a tired man with a morning commitment. The magneto's fault was confirmed on a bench twelve hours later. Everyone arrived; not everything about how was free.</p>
<h3>ADM analysis</h3>
<p>The aviation decision was sound and the bench proved it. The transportation decision that replaced the flight deserves its own honest look: risk didn't vanish when the airplane stayed chained, it changed vehicles. A fatigued night drive is statistically no one's safe harbor. The instructive part is jurisdictional: in the airplane, the risk was yours to accept or refuse for both of you, and you refused it; on the road, it was his, in his own domain, made with open eyes and his own hands on the wheel. PIC authority is total and it is also bounded. Knowing where it ends is part of carrying it well.</p>
<h3>What good judgment looks like here</h3>
<p>Solve the passenger's real problem with him before he solves it alone: lay out the drive, the continuance, and the morning flight as honest options with honest costs. You did the aviation half cleanly. The version of this ending with nothing to examine is the one where the continuance got one more minute of your advocacy: the deposition moved once in this scenario's other branches, and nobody died of it.</p>
<h3>Key takeaway</h3>
<p>Grounding the airplane moves the risk; it doesn't retire it. Finish the job: help the mission die completely or move safely, not just leave your cockpit.</p>
</div>
